bug.short_desc: [Regression] Eclipse is freezed when chart has too small size [13]

long_desc.thetext:
Created attachment 86801 report design
Description: Eclipse is freezed when resize the chart using cube.
Build number: 2.2.2.v20080111-0630
Steps to reproduce: 1. Open the attached report design and change the chart width to 3.
Expected result: Chart is resized.
Actual result: Eclipse is freezed until it is restarted.
Error log: N/A
It has nothing to do with chart with cube binding. If chart has too small size, there may be something wrong with rendering.
It is a regression that something wrong happens when rendering a chart of too small size.

Phenomenon: Freeze happens when: the legend uses vertical orientation and height of the chart is too small; or the legend uses horizontal orientation and the width of the chart is too small.
Reason: Some logic errors cause endless loop in Legendbuilder.
Solution: fixed.
